==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wall Street
<hw>Wall Street</hw>. <def>A street towards the southern end of the
borough of Manhattan, New York City, extending from Broadway to the East
River; -- so called from the old wall which extended along it when the
city belonged to the Dutch. It is the chief financial center of the
United States, hence the name is often used for the money market and the
financial interests of the country; -- in American financial
publications, also referred to as <altname>the
street</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

